This is an agent orchestration server , using MCP protocol to extend context knowledge about the code base, build logical agent missions and helping a developer with managing multiple agents running simultaniously.  It is also a task manager, which can quickly collect tasks while coding as a technical deb tracker or activity tracker, these tasks can alter be converted into projects. 

GiljoAi Agent Orchestration MCP Server is a multi-agent orchestration system that transforms AI coding assistants into coordinated
  development teams. It breaks through context limits by orchestrating multiple specialized agents that work
  together on complex tasks. The system acts as a persistent brain that manages state, memory, and coordination
  while Claude Code (or other AI assistants) provides the execution engine. Agents can spawn sub-agents with
  specific roles, share context through a priority-based message queue, hand off tasks intelligently, and
  collaborate on projects that would exceed a single agent's context window. It includes a PostgreSQL-backed
  architecture for multi-tenant project management, a REST API with WebSocket support for real-time updates, and a
  Vue.js dashboard for monitoring agent activity - making it possible to tackle enterprise-scale coding projects
  with AI assistance.


